reviewText: I didn't know this was a reissued DVD since I didn't ever see it the first time around.  I love this one.  I like it that it's just her with no others.  I like it that she doesn't use any stretchies, hand weights or balls, and there are a few different moves in here that I haven't seen in any of her others.  I think it's one of her best! :)

reviewText: This is an awesome DVD.  Ms. Sansone not only gives you a great workout, but she gives some powerful advice as well.  The 500 steps before each meal was great advice.  I went out and bought a pedometer and it made me caution of how much walking I was doing per day.  This DVD is also a good way to get in a quick mile if you have a lot to do.  You can just do the 500 steps 4 times and that's one whole mile in just a few minutes.  The introduction was an eye opener to me as well.  In that she shows you what five pounds of body fat actually looks like.  That in itself is a motivator to make you want to get up and walk away the pounds.  When I first started using Leslie Sansone Walk at Home program, I was weighing 207 pounds.  Today I am at 154.  My goal is 140.  The only thing I do is walk to her DVDs and I changed to a healthier eating pattern.  I have Walk Your Belly Flat, Walk Away Your Waistline, Walk Yourself Slim, Four Fast Miles and so many more.  Any DVD that you get will be a great tool to begin with.  There are only four basic steps, so if you are like me and have no rhythm, the DVDs are just perfect because there are not a lot of steps to learn, and she encourages you to go at your own pace.  The only thing she wants you to do is keep moving, because as long as long as you are moving, you are burning calories.  So go get that DVD and walk yourself to a slimmer, more healthier you.  If I can do it, I know anybody can!
summary: Walk Off Ten Pounds, Awesome DVD!

reviewText: It's okay. There are some moments of sloppy cuing.The major thing is to beware the mileage claim. The last mile is way slower than the first but is done in less time than the first. Seems sketchy. Also, she goes into a stretch in the last 3 minutes of the walk without making it clear if the 3 miles are done. Surely she's not counting the meager steps in the stretch towards the mileage.By the 2.5 mile point, you will feel more like you're in cool down mode.As an aside, Leslie would fare better if she would go full out for the total mileage and then slow down in a separate cool down walk and stretch.

reviewText: I have about every Leslie Sansone product out there and I even hung in there when the first couple of bad videos started coming out but it's just too much lately...she has shifted from quality to quantity and is just pushing anything out the door to make more money and it's not at all the feeling I had when I first started using her products.  I used to feel like I was part of a team now I just feel like I'm being used, especially after I went to her site and saw they only offer clothing up to a size XL.  Why is that she is willing to make a living off people who are above an XL but they aren't good enough to provide clothing for?This is not a new video, it's a repackaged one and that is a cheap move in my eyes.
summary: I'm done with Leslie Sansone Products

reviewText: I too am disgusted with this dishonest practice of repackaging workouts to fool the buyer. With all the products Sansone sells and all the DVDs, I wonder how desperate she is for money. I have about 10 of her workouts and after buying the latest one -- 3 Mega Miles -- I don't know if I'll buy another. It's sloppy, you can barely hear the music and feels like she threw it together without much thought. I use 4 other aerobics instructor's DVDs and they are by far superior. They are more challenging, much better produced and their workouts are clean and flawless. Also they don't do all that annoying chatting. I still get a decent workout from Sansone. I just had to get this off my chest. I really hope she will put some thought and time into her next DVD.
summary: How Much Money Does Sansone Have to Make?

reviewText: This 3 Mile DVD is apart of her Walk Your Way Slim Series available from Target.com and is well worth the investment! I literally just finished this DVD and am so extremely glad that I purchased this along with 3 others from the 6-Kit Series. In fact, I think I am going to purchase the remaining 2 kits as this makes the 3rd one that I love!Walk Off 10 Pounds is like I said a 3 Mile DVD done at an Intermediate to Advanced pace. There isn't any boosted walking (jogging) in this workout, but the pace is faster and you do some powerful movements. One of the things that I have noticed with several of her newer releases in 2009 is that she does a move called Power Kicks. These are done at a vigorous intensity and are bwt low and high impact. You barely leave the ground, but you kick fast and high. You will do grapevines, 4 counts walking up and back several times, some with a kick sequence thrown in with them, side steps with taps and heels, ect. The variety is here so it is a little more than the Basic 4. 3 Mile Slim & Sleek still has the newer "moves" but this still gives you easy choreography without the same ol', same ol'. If you have other Kits from this Series or the Burn Body Fat Series, you will notice that much of the music is the same, however not all songs are repeated within 4 kits that I have, not sure about all 6 at this point. You will find a solid cool down of about 2 minutes perhaps a little more and a nice stretch. The set is black but she has those Stability Balls on the set with her and they are colored coordinated to her wardrobe: Yellow, Black, and Charcoal. You will occasionally be able to see outside and there is snow on the ground; fun for me as I was looking in my own backyard with snow. I thought that was cute.I word of caution: in the first Mile there are a couple of cueing flubs. I'm used to walking with her I don't notice them too often anymore. 1 mistake is she said to do knee lifts but does kicks instead. She catches herself at the end of the kicks and apologizes for the mistake. I didn't even notice it myself until she pointed it out. The second mishap is she instructors you to do side steps then goes automatically into a double side step. Again no biggie and she giggles about it. You can't help but smile. Those are the things that keep you on your toes and add a little laughter into your day! Why get upset when you could just smile and go with the flow?Because of the pace more so than the cueing, I would tell beginners to try her 2 Mile DVDs first or to get her Walk Off Even More Weight Kit which offers 2-2 Mile Walks; a Classic and a Faster Paced walk. Those will get you up to the speed and endurance that you will need for her 3+ Mile DVDs. You could go right into her 3 Milers, but it may be too advanced to begin with. This DVD like her recent ones allow you to pick the Chapter you wish. You can choose Mile 1, Mile 2, or Mile 3. You though cannot customize the DVDs and you have to fast forward/rewind to get to the warm up and cool down sections if you did not choose the first or 3rd miles.What's included in this kit? DVD, Purple Pedometer, and a 14 Day Meal Plan. In the DVD Leslie instructs you to eat the meals in the plan that you like! Customize it to fit your needs! She reminds us that we can still eat the foods that we love and lose weight; it's just watching portions and making better choices most of the time. She goes on to say that she doesn't like a lot of "rules" as we know what does or doesn't feel right. What I loved most about this DVD was its Positive Message and overall tone! She tells you to "Have and Excuse-Free Day"! That you have the choice to improve your life! If you are able to get out of bed she says, then you are already healthy. Movement improves your health, mood, physical and spiritual fitness! She also reminds you to forget and let go of the negativity in your life; let go of the negativity that people share. Forgive than, let go, and move on. They don't know what they are doing so no need to be upset or set back by other's negativity. I think an equally moving and important message is that even just losing 5 pounds makes a difference in how you feel. That you don't need to rush yourself and overwhelm yourself with huge weight loss goals, just take it one step a time; 5 pounds at a time. It doesn't matter how long it takes, just make better choices for your health and you will reap the rewards!Absolutely a wonderful walking workout! I have truly become a total fan of the Leslie-Only, non-walk leader Workouts. She's able to give you calm direction and coaching as she puts it. It's true! I feel fabulous not only because of the workout, but because of her positive and motivating words!! This is a DVD to own! Great message, great pace, great advice, warm, caring instructor, and positive well being!

reviewText: questo workout è meraviglioso... io ho quasi tutti i suoi allenamenti e li adoro tutti forse perchè  grazie a lei ho perso tanto ma tanto di quel peso da un anno a questa parte che la ringrazierò per sempre... questo in particolare è stupendo anche se io non amo il suo studio nero mi deprime sinceramente questo è meglio degli altri perchè almeno qui si vede dallo specchio la sua cucina, c'è un bel tappeto con un divano e poi la musica è stupenda.. io di solito lavoravo molto con i suoi 4 o 5 miglia ma debbo dire che questi ultimi 3 miglia sono molto più belli e io sudo di più. alla fine di questo allenamento sono sudatissima molto di più rispetto a un suo 4 miglia. questo è simile alla serie slim come intensità. grazie ai suoi allenamenti son dimagrita quasi 30 kg e mi ha cambiato la vita. Io non amo la palestra non l'ho mai amata preferisco allenarmi nella mia casa e poi farmi una doccia in tranquillità per iniziare la giornata. magari poi aggiungo un dvd di Denise Austin altra ottima istruttrice.Grazie Leslie per accompagnarmi costantemente nella mia perdita di peso.

reviewText: I have worked out with Leslie for years and will probably continue because her style is vigorous without killing my knees. But I really hate her sloppy cueing and how she tries to make it look OK. It's NOT OK. If there was one worst Leslie offering this would have to be it. In this DVD she tries to bluff her way out by saying things like, "Yay!", "Yeah!" and "Do X when your feet are ready" when she jumps into a move without giving her 'class' time to jump in with her. She rambles her philosophies right through many arm movements, again, not cueing them. Leslie should really be more professional. It's awful to come home after a long day to work out to a sloppy DVD.
